title: Taser effects on bare skin in super slow-motion, on The Feed!
text:
Some of the latest and greatest viral videos include a shocking slow-mo study and a dog's snowy adventure.
At TASER headquarters in Scottsdale, Arizona, Gavin Free, one of the two Slow Mo Guys, is documenting what the electroshock weapon does to bare skin -- in super slow-motion, of course. Utilizing cameras that take 28,500 high-definition pictures per second, you can literally see the pain sink in. Interesting fact: Every piece confetti that explodes when the taser is fired, contains the serial number of the cartridge that fired it, making it easy to trace back the history of the firing incident.
Loki the Wolfdog is a beautiful, snow-loving Husky-Arctic Wolf-Malamute-mix. This majestic footage was taken while playing with his owner mostly in passes of the Rocky Mountains in central Colorado. Check out Loki's Instagram page. It's breath-taking.
